			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>Debugging in Domain-Specific Modelling</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/RaphaelMannadiar.html">Raphael Mannadiar</a>, <a href="../profile/HansVangheluwe.html">Hans Vangheluwe</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_17">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_17</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The main contribution is tooling support for debugging in DSML environments.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> Debugging features are motivated by improving usability and developer experience when working with DSMLs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The setting and requirements are specific to domain-specific modeling languages.
</li></ul></li></ul>
